808.x QUOTATIONS INDEX
A unified reference for all literary‑form quotation classes in Domain‑Papers.

808.81 — Poetry quotations
Quotations drawn from poetic works, verse forms, epics, lyric poetry, and metrical compositions.
Use when the source text is primarily poetic in structure.

808.82 — Drama quotations
Quotations from plays, scripts, stage works, and dramatic literature.
Use when the source text is intended for performance.

808.83 — Fiction quotations
Quotations from novels, novellas, short stories, and fictional prose.
Use when the source text is narrative prose.

808.84 — Essays quotations
Quotations from essays, reflective prose, and analytical literary commentary.
Use when the source text is nonfiction prose with a reflective or argumentative structure.

808.85 — Speeches quotations
Quotations from speeches, orations, public addresses, and rhetorical performances.
Use when the source text is spoken rhetoric.

808.86 — Letters quotations
Quotations from correspondence, personal letters, epistolary works, and written communications.
Use when the source text is epistolary.

808.87 — Mixed literary forms
Quotations from hybrid works combining multiple literary forms (e.g., verse‑prose blends, experimental structures).
Use when the source text does not fit cleanly into a single form.

808.88 — Miscellaneous quotations
General quotations not tied to a specific literary form.
Use when the source text is uncategorized, multi‑form, or general.

